            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] the son of the music master Zhi Kui of the You Yu lineage. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">Zi gao asked: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">How did he become emperor?" </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">Confucius said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">"In antiquity they did not trasnmit it (=the throne) from father to son, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">good people would receive it from each other, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">so they could order all under Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en">pacify the miriad states, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en">let those who have not and those who have, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en">the few and the many, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en">the fat [=strong] and the weak, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en">let them all attain their altars of soil and grain </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en">and [let] the hundred clans respectfully to preserve these (altars). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en">Yao saw Shun's virtue and worth, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en">therefore he yield it (to him). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">Zi Gao said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">"That Yao obtained Shun, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">was it because Shun's virtue was really good? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">Or becasue Yao's virtue was extraordinarily enlightened? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">Confucius said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">"It was both. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en">Shun was harvesting in a field of barren soil, but [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en">[...] (one) of the black headed people from the barren soil. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">Confucius said: [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">I have heard that Shun in his youth, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">would brightly treat his kin with filial piety (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">some became estranged because of distress [but not Shun]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">When Yao adopted Shun, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">he followed him in the middle of the wilderness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">he talked with him about ritual </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">was pleased to be close... (?) [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">- </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">(During) the travels of the earlier kings </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">the way did not meet with demise, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">and the kings too did not (meet with) big upheavals (?). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">Confucius said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">“Shun truly can be said “to have received the mandate”, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">Shun was son of a man [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en">[and yet] the three kings served him. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] (?) and harmonious, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">therefore Shun’s virtue was really that of a worthy, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">he (Yao) took him from amidst the fields </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">and let him rule all under Heaven- </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">thereby he became famous. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">Zi Gao said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">“Should Shun be in our generation, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en">how would it be? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en">Confucius said: [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">Zi Gao asked Confucius: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">“As for the rise of the three kings, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">they were in each case sons of men, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">and their father was of low status </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">and not deserving fame? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">Or were they also true sons of Heaven?” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en">Confucius said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en">“Good question! </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-6a.9" xml:lang="en">It has been long, that nobody [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en">(Yu’s mother was the daughter of the You Zai lineage), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en">she looked at Yi </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en">and got pregnant of him (Yu), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en">and after a pregnancy of three years </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en">he was born through a split in her back, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en">when he was born he could speak, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-7a.7" xml:lang="en">this was Yu. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en">Qi’s mother was the daughter of the You Song clan. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en">She went on an excursion up the Yang tower, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en">there was a swallow with an egg in her mouth </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en">and placed it in front of her, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en">she took it and swallowed it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en">and after a pregnancy of three years he was born through a split in her breast, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.7" xml:lang="en">when he was born he cried: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.8" xml:lang="en">khem”! ??? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-8a.9" xml:lang="en">This was Qi. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en">Hou Ji’s mother was the daughter of the You Tai clan. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en">She went on an excursion in the black Hills, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en">it was winter and she saw a herb, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en">she plucked it and presented it (to the Lord), ??? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.5" xml:lang="en">then she saw human footprints, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.6" xml:lang="en">she stepped on them and prayed: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.7" xml:lang="en">“Lord’s foot prints, may you do so that [...].” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0036_tls_001-9a.8" xml:lang="en">This was Hou Ji’s (mother). </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
